external_knowledge:
- "specific kind" refers to sensors with a type ID of 1; 
- "operated after the start of 2023" means the data collection started after '2023-01-01T00:00:00.000'; 
- "typical performance on metric A" represents the arithmetic mean of A values collected.

sql:
SELECT sd.data_id
FROM sensor_data sd
WHERE sd.A > (SELECT AVG(A) FROM sensor_data);

SELECT type_name
FROM sensor_types
WHERE min_value > -40 AND max_value < 350;

SELECT version_id, version_date, version_number, version_notes
FROM data_versions
ORDER BY version_date DESC;

external_knowledge:
- "active sensor types" refers to sensors currently in operation and not in maintenance or decommissioned;
- "data since the start of 2023" indicates that the collection time (`time_start`) must be on or after January 1, 2023;
- "average of metric A exceeding two hundred" means the average value for metric A (`AVG(sd.A)`) must be above 200 for the sensor type to be considered.
